    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "routines don't help though. they just feel like i'm going through the motions of a life i don't even recognize anymore. everything he did, everything we built... it's all just dead weight now. it feels like i'm just dragging this heavy, pointless existence around for no reason at all. it's just so exhausting to keep pretending that there's a \"next chapter\" when the story is already over.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
